 past. Feng had threaten to kill Wang with his new dagger the day before the attack, after the two were in an online argument in a chatroom. The victim bleed to death due to the lack of emergency treatment. He was pronounced dead at the hospital the same day as the attack, at 2:50 p.m. The school was accused of failing to save the victim. No school teachers, faculties, or staffs tried to perform first-aid on Wang, and neither did they call emergency services, despite knowing about the incident. Wang was transported to hospital with help of his classmates. The on-campus doctor resumed teaching her art class, knowing Wang was bleeding heavily. The school administration refused to accept any media nor did they apologise for the incident.\n|-\n| February 27, 2012\n|[[Chardon, Ohio|Chardon]],<br>[[Ohio]],<br>United States\n| T.J. Lane, 17\n| 3 dead\n| 3 injured\n|[[Chardon High School shooting]]. Six students were shot at Chardon High School. One student, Daniel Parmentor, died at the scene, and on February 28, two other students, Russell King and Demetrius Hewlin, also died. One of the three others wounded was in critical condition. The shooter, Thomas \"T.J.\" Lane, was taken into police custody. Lane was reported to have had a \"rivalry\" with King, although was unfamiliar with any other victims. In March 2013, Lane was convicted of the crimes and was sentenced to life in prison without parole.\n|-\n| March 1, 2012\n| [[Sulaimaniyah]], [[Kurdistan]], [[Iraq]]\n| Biyar Sarwar, 18\n| 2 dead\n| \n| 18-year-old Biyar Sarwar shot American gym teacher Jeremiah Small three times in the head and chest at Medes High School, a private Christian academy school. Small died in the classroom. Biyar then turned the gun on himself and fired another round into his head, and was pronounced dead in hospital.<ref>{{cite news|title=American teacher gunned down by Iraqi student at Christian school in the nation\u2019s Kurdish region|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2108753/American-teacher-Jeremiah-Small-killed-student-Christian-school-Iraq.html|accessdate=September 1, 2013|location=London|work=Daily Mail|date=March 1, 2012}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 1, 2012\n|[[Chicago]], [[Illinois]], United States\n| Christian Gonzalez, 17\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n|17-year-old Chris Wormley was stabbed to death on the front steps of AMIKids Infinity Charter School. Another 17-year-old student was arrested. The suspect was charged as an adult with murder and attempted murder.<ref>{{cite news|title=Student dies after stabbing incident at Chicago school\n|url=http://www.cnn.com/2012/03/01/justice/illinois-school-stabbing|date=March 1, 2012|accessdate=September 1, 2013|work=CNN}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Christian Gonzalez, Chicago Teen Charged In Fatal Stabbing, Claims He Was Bullied (VIDEO)|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/03/04/christian-gonzalez-chicag_n_1319469.html|accessdate=March 4, 2012|date=September 1, 2013|work=Huffington Post|first=Joseph|last=Erbentraut}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 19, 2012\n| [[Toulouse]], [[France]]\n| Mohammed Merah, 23\n| 4 dead\n| 1 injured\n|[[2012 Midi-Pyr\u00e9n\u00e9es shootings]]. As part of a series of three gun attacks in Toulouse and [[Montauban]], an Islamic French citizen who claimed to be a member of [[al-Qaeda]] shot and killed three children and one Rabbi, and seriously injured another student at the Ozar Hatorah Jewish day school.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/03/24/opinion/loner-loser-killer.html?scp=1&sq=olivier%20roy&st=cse&_r=0 |work=The New York Times | first=Olivier | last=Roy | title=Loner, Loser, Killer | date=March 23, 2012}}</ref> \n|-\n| May 19, 2012\n| [[Brindisi]], [[Italy]]\n| Giovanni Vantaggiato, 68\n| 1 dead\n| 5 injured\n|[[2012 Brindisi school bombing]]. A three gas cylinder bomb hidden in a large rubbish bin exploded in front of the Morvillo Falcone high school in Brindisi, Italy, killing one 16-year-old female student and injuring five others \u2013 one seriously. The bombe