e dormitories. This attack was part of a wave of arsons at dormitories in a Kenya at the time, although the overwhelming majority were harmless. In 2017, at least 126 high schools in Kenya experienced arson attacks, in what appeared to be protests by students over the shortening of holidays and limiting of visits by parents. Schools claimed to be taking those measures after a recent trend in previous years of widespread cheating in high school final-year exams. Students were also protesting harsh discipline at schools, poor teaching and corruption. The attacks were also linked to disputes over senior appointments in schools.<ref>{{Cite web |url= https://www.reuters.com/article/us-kenya-school-fire/arson-caused-fire-at-kenyan-school-that-killed-nine-girls-minister-idUSKCN1BF0YI</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-41145324</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2017/09/students-killed-nairobi-school-fire-170902064249327.html</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|September 13, 2017}}\n|[[Rockford, Washington]], US \n| Student \n| 1 dead\n| 3 injured\n| A student opened fire at [[Freeman High School (Washington)|Freeman High School]], killing one and wounding three others. He was arrested afterward.<ref>{{cite news|title=1 dead, 3 hurt in shooting at Spokane-area high school|url=http://www.oregonlive.com/pacific-northwest-news/index.ssf/2017/09/shooting_reported_at_freeman_h.html|newspaper=Oregon Live|agency=Associated Press|date=September 13, 2017|accessdate=September 13, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|September 14, 2017}}\n| [[Kampung Datuk Keramat]], [[Kuala Lumpur]], [[Malaysia]]\n| Seven students \n| 23 killed\n| 5 injured \n| At around 5:10 am on 14 September 2017, a fire was set by seven student at the dorms of the Darul Quran Ittifaqiyah madrasa in Kampung Datuk Keramat, Kuala Lumpur, which resulted in 23 of the madrasa residents (comprising 21 students and two teachers) killed, while five others were injured. Most of the suspects were apprehended on 16 September. The suspects were believed to have committed the crime out of revenge due to taunting among the students of the madrasa and the suspects. Six out of seven suspects were tested positive for drugs and two of them had previous criminal records relating to rioting and stealing vehicles. All suspects were aged between 11 and 18 years old. <ref>{{Cite web |url=http://mobile.abc.net.au/news/2017-09-16/seven-teens-arrested-over-malaysia-boarding-school-fire/8953680}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|September 20, 2017}}\n|[[Mattoon, Illinois]], US\n| Student, 14\n| \n| 1 injured\n| A 14-year-old male student attending[[Mattoon High School]] was subdued by a female teacher when he attempted to open fire in the school cafeteria at 11:33&nbsp;a.m. Multiple shots were fired in the process, and one student was struck in the chest. The victim was driven to a nearby hospital suffering non-life-threatening wounds. The suspect was taken into custody without further incident.<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.mattoon.k12.il.us/vnews/display.v/ART/59c2b2193096f |title = Mattoon Community Unit School District 2 \u2013 MHS students, staff secure following shooting |website= www.mattoon.k12.il.us |language = en |access-date = September 21, 2017 |url-status = live |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20170921144403/https://www.mattoon.k12.il.us/vnews/display.v/ART/59c2b2193096f |archivedate = September 21, 2017 |df = mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url = http://time.com/4950377/mattoon-illinois-high-school-shooting/ |title = Suspect in Custody After Injuring One in Shooting at Illinois High School |last = Press |first = Associated |website= Time |access-date = September 21, 2017 |url-status = dead |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20170920231817/http://time.com/4950377/mattoon-illinois-high-school-shooting/ |archivedate = September 20, 2017 |df = mdy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Dts|September 26, 2017}}\n|[[Bronx, New York]], US \n| Student, 18\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| Abel 