ster B. Pearson High School (Calgary)|Lester B. Pearson High School]] in Calgary by a 16-year-old student. The 16-year-old was later convicted of second-degree murder and sentenced to four years imprisonment.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/canada/story/2000/11/22/calgary_stab001122.html |archive-url=https://archive.today/20120730143438/http://www.cbc.ca/canada/story/2000/11/22/calgary_stab001122.html |archive-date=2012-07-30 |title=Hundred mourn teenager in Calgary |publisher=Cbc.ca |date=2000-11-23 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/story/2001/04/26/jaberca260401.html |title=Teen gets 4 years for Jaber death |publisher=Cbc.ca |date=2001-04-26 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| January 18, 2001\n| [[Bromma borough|Bromma]], [[Stockholm]], Sweden\n| ..., 17\n..., 19\n| 1 dead\n|\n| A 16-year-old student was shot to death in a toilet facility of the [[Bromma borough|Bromma]] [[Gymnasium (school)|Gymnasium]], in [[Stockholm]], Sweden. Two other students, ages 17 and 19, were charged with the murder.<ref name=\"apsweden118\">{{cite news|first=Stephhan|last=Nasstrom|title=Teen-Ager Shot to Death in Sweden|date=2001-01-18|url =http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P1-39966865.html|archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20121106054737/http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P1-39966865.html|url-status =dead|archive-date =2012-11-06|agency =[[Associated Press]]|accessdate = 2009-04-18}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 5, 2001\n| [[Santee, California]], United States\n| [[Charles Andrew Williams]], 15\n| 2 dead\n| 13 injured\n| Armed with a [[.22|.22-caliber]] [[revolver]], 15-year-old Charles Andrew Williams opened fire in a male toilet facility at [[Santana High School]] in [[Santee, California]], killing one student. Then exiting the restroom, Williams fired indiscriminately at nearby students, killing another student and wounding 13. Shortly afterward he retreated back into the restroom, where he surrendered to police. In June 2002, Wil