, Oregon]], United States\n| Chad Escobedo, 15\n|\n| 10 injured\n| High school freshman Chad Escobedo shoots the windows out of two classrooms from outside Springwater Trail High School injuring ten students with [[Fragmentation (weaponry)|shrapnel]] and broken glass, two of which required stitches. His motive was to shoot at a class in which he was enrolled, unhappy that the instructor had called his parents; the classrooms he hit, however, were not his intended target.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theoutlookonline.com/news/story.php?story_id=117652056556535900 |title=Shooter was \u2018crying out for help,\u2019 friends say |publisher=Theoutlookonline.com |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| April 18, 2007\n| [[Huntersville, North Carolina]], United States\n| Josh Emerson Cook, 16\n| 1 dead\n|\n| A 16-year-old threatened two students in the parking lot at North Mecklenberg High School with a gun, and shortly afterwards, had shot himself at a local gas station when confronted by police.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wbtv.com/home/7083871.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080203224300/http://www.wbtv.com/home/7083871.html|url-status=dead|title=North Mecklenburg High School Student Dead|archivedate=February 3, 2008}}</ref> Four Charlotte-Mecklenberg schools went on lockdown.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.policeone.com/school-violence/articles/1238487-N-C-high-school-student-shoots-self-after-he-is-confronted-by-police/|title=N.C. high school student shoots self after he is confronted by police|website=policeone.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| May 15, 2007\n| [[Maoming]], [[China]]\n| Wu Jianguo, 17\n| 2 dead\n| 4 injured\n| 17-year-old Wu Jianguo stabbed six classmates with a knife at Dianbai County No. 3 Middle School, killing two of them.<ref>[http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2007-05/18/content_875126.htm 2 dead in stabbing attack], ''[[China Daily]]'' (May 18, 2007)</ref>\n|-\n| May 23, 2007\n| [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], Canada\n| ..., 17;<br>..., 17\n| 1 dead\n|