rome]]||Sprinter||{{Post-nominals|country=CAN|OC}}; school teacher and track and field runner who competed in three Olympic Games, the British Empire and Commonwealth Games and the Pan-American Games during the 1960s||<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://olympic.ca/team-canada/harry-jerome/|title=Harry Jerome|publisher=Team Canada - Official Olympic Website|website=olympic.ca|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Victoria Jurgens]]||Politician||Represented the [[Saskatchewan Party]] from 2011-2016 in the [[Prince Albert Northcote]] riding.||<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://panow.com/2019/05/28/former-mla-seeks-local-sask-party-nomination/|title=Former MLA seeks local Sask. Party nomination|last=Maxwell|first=Nigel|date=May 28, 2019|publisher=PANow|accessdate=April 12, 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===K===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- align=left\n! style=\"width:20%;\"|Name\n! style=\"width:20%;\"|Occupation\n! style=\"width:60%;\"|Notes\n! style=\"width:20%;\"|Ref\n|-\n|[[Marliese Kasner]]||Curler and teacher||[[2003 World Junior Curling Championships|2003]] World Junior Champion and former member of her sister [[Stefanie Lawton]]'s team.||<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldcurl.com/player.php?playerid=612|title=Marliese Kasner|publisher=[[World Curling Tour]] - Powered by CurlingZone|accessdate=April 19, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Boris Karloff]]||Actor||Known for his roles in horror films portraying characters like [[Frankenstein]]'s Monster and [[The Mummy (1932 film)|The Mummy]]; resided in Prince Albert during the early 20th century; applied to Harry St. Clair of Prince Albert's Harry St. Clair players and toured with them between 1912 and 1914 before becoming famous in Hollywood||<ref>{{cite web | title = Tourism Prince Albert&nbsp;\u2014 Our Proud History | url = http://www.patourism.ca/history.aspx | accessdate =March 16, 2008 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080304065407/http://www.patourism.ca/history.aspx <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = March 4, 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Jacobs |first=Stephen |title=Boris Karloff in Alberta |year=2007 |url=http://www.morethanamonster.com/Boris%20Karloff%20in%20Alberta.pdf |format=PDF |accessdate=May 22, 2009|url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714114432/http://www.morethanamonster.com/Boris%20Karloff%20in%20Alberta.pdf |archivedate=July 14, 2011 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite book | last = Buehrer | first =Beverley Bare  | title = Boris Karloff By  | publisher=Greenwood Publishing Group | year = 1993 | location = |isbn=9780313277153 |format= published on line by Google books | page = 5 | url = https://books.google.com/?id=nmd77kTyX_oC&pg=PA5&lpg=PA5&dq=%22Boris+Karloff%22++%22Prince+Albert%22 }}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Andrew Knox (Canadian politician)|Andrew Knox]]||Politican and farmer||He represented [[Prince Albert (electoral district)|Prince Albert]] in the [[House of Commons of Canada]] from 1917 to 1925. He was elected to Parliament in the [[1917 Canadian federal election|1917 federal election]] as a [[Liberal-Unionist]] supporter of Sir [[Robert Borden]]'s wartime [[Unionist Party (Canada)|Union Government]]. After the war, he [[crossed the floor]] to join the new [[Progressive Party of Canada|Progressive Party]].||<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://https://lop.parl.ca/sites/ParlInfo/default/en_CA/People/Profile?personId=10414|title=Profile <nowiki>|</nowiki> Knox, Andrew|publisher=Parlinfo - Parliament of Canada|website=parl.ca|accessdate=April 19, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Kirk Krack]]||Freediver||Broke records throughout his career; created Performance Freediving International, Canadian Association of Freediving and Apnea; founding member of the United States Apnea Association; organized many competitions; head safety for the Cayman Challenge; has done film and TV work associated with freediving||<ref>{{cite web| title = Kirk Krack bio| publisher = Performance Freediving International| url = http://www.performancefreediving.com/team-bios/kirk-krack/| doi = | acce