ina.ca/entry/steuart_david_gordon_1916-.html|archive-date=February 12, 2012|url-status= dead}}</ref>\n\n|-\n|[[Norman Sheldon]]||Soccer player||Scottish immigrant that played on Team Canada in the early 1900s.  He is a member of both the Saskatchewan and Prince Albert Sports Halls of Fame.||<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://sasksportshalloffame.com/inductees/norman-sheldon/|title=Norman \"Norm\" Sheldon|publisher=Saskatchewan Sports Hall of Fame|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[John Stevenson (Saskatchewan politician)|John Stevenson]]||Politician||Liberal MLA and Senator||\n|}\n\n===T===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- align=left\n! style=\"width:20%;\"|Name\n! style=\"width:20%;\"|Occupation\n! style=\"width:60%;\"|Notes\n! style=\"width:20%;\"|Ref\n|-\n|[[Richard Tapper (swimmer)|Richard Tapper]]||Swimmer||Competed for [[New Zealand at the 1992 Summer Olympics|New Zealand]] at the [[1992 Summer Olympics]]||\n|-\n|[[Allan R. Taylor]]||Banker||{{Post-nominals|country=CAN|OC}}; banker who was inducted into the [[Canadian Business Hall of Fame]] in 2006.||<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cbhf.ca/allan-r-taylor-oc-cbhf-class-2006|title=Allan R. Taylor <nowiki>|</nowiki>CBHF|publisher=[[Canadian Business Hall of Fame]]|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Joey Tetarenko]]||Hockey player || Played in the NHL for [[Florida Panthers]], [[Carolina Hurricanes]], and Ottawa Senators||<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hockeydb.com/ihdb/stats/pdisplay.php?pid=19317|title=Joey Tetarenko Hockey Stats and Profile at hockeydb.com|publisher=HockeyDB.com|website=hockeydb.com|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Kara Thevenot]]||Curler||Bronze medalist at the [[[[2019 Scotties Tournament of Hearts|2019]] [[Scotties Tournament of Hearts]].||<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldcurl.com/player.php?playerid=22625|title=Kara Thevenot|publisher=[[World Curling Tour]] - Powered by CurlingZone|accessdate=April 19, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Jesse Thistle]]||Author and professor||Authored the best-selling memoir ''From the Ashes'' and is assistant professor in the Department of Equity Studies at [[York University]].  His post-secondary education includes a Bachelor of Liberal Arts and Professional Studies with a Specialized Honours in History from York University in 2015, Masters of History at the [[University of Waterloo]] in 2016, and PhD in the History Department at York University.||<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://jessethistle.com/about/|title=About - Jesse Thistle|publisher=Jesse Thistle|website=jessethistle.com|accessdate=April 12, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Max Thompson (skier)|Max Thompson]]||[[Nordic combined|Nordic combined skier]]||Has competed nationally and internationally at the Olympics||<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://olympic.ca/team-canada/max-thompson/|title=Max Thompson|publisher=Team Canada - Official Olympic Team Website|website=olympic.ca|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Ken Tralnberg]]||Curler and curling coach||Silver medalist at the [[2002 Winter Olympics]].  He coached the Swiss Women's Curling team at the 2010 Winter Olympics in Vancouver as well as their coach at the 2014 Winter Olympics in Sochi.||<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://olympic.ca/team-canada/kenneth-tralnberg/|title=Kenneth Tralnberg|publisher=Team Canada - Official Olympic Team Website|website=olympic.ca|accessdate=April 19, 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===U===\n\n===V===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- align=left\n! style=\"width:20%;\"|Name\n! style=\"width:20%;\"|Occupation\n! style=\"width:60%;\"|Notes\n! style=\"width:20%;\"|Ref\n|-\n|[[Doyle Vermette]]||Politician||MLA for [[New Democratic Party of Saskatchewan|NDP]] in the [[Cumberland (Saskatchewan provincial electoral district)|Cumberland]] riding.  He was first elected in 2008.||<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndpcaucus.sk.ca/doylevermette|title=Doyle Vermette - Saskatchewan NDP Caucus|publisher=Saskatchewan NDP Caucus|accessdate=April 12, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Jon Vickers]]||Opera singer||{{Post-nominals|country=CAN|CC}}; a distinguished tenor; born in Prince Albert||<ref>''Jon Vickers: A Hero\u2019s Life'' by Jeannie Williams, Northeastern University Press, 1999. {{ISBN|1-55553-408-2}}</ref>\n|-  style=\"vertical-align:top; background:#ffffec;\"\n|}\n\n===W===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- align=left\n! style=\"width:20%;\"|Name\n! style=\"width:20%;\"|Occupation\n! style=\"width:60%;\"|Notes\n! style=\"width:20%;\"|Ref\n|-\n|[[Owen Walter]]||Hockey player||Awarded the 2003 [[Brown University]] Charles A. Robinson Memorial Trophy for academic achievement before playing professionally||<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.brownbears.com/sports/m-hockey/History/Robinson_Trophy|title=Brown Men's Hockey Charles A. Robinson Memorial Trophy|work=brownbears.com|access-date=2015-04-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170722022716/http://brownbears.com/sports/m-hockey/History/Robinson_Trophy|archive-date=2017-07-22|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[George Weaver (politician)|George Weaver]]||Politician and metallurgical engineer||||<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mhs.mb.ca/docs/people/weaver_gd.shtml|title=Memorial Manitoba: George Dyer Weaver (1908-1986)|publisher=Manitoba Historical Society|accessdate=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Rick Wilson (ice hockey)|Rick Wilson]]||Hockey player||Retired professional ice hockey defenceman and [[head coach]]; currently an [[assistant coach]] with the [[Dallas Stars]]||<ref>{{cite web | title = Legends of Hockey \u2013 NHL Player Search \u2013 Player \u2013 Rick Wilson | publisher = Hockey Hall of Fame and Museum| url = http://www.legendsofhockey.net:8080/LegendsOfHockey/jsp/SearchPlayer.jsp?player=14707 | accessdate = May 22, 2009 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20060714215046/http://www.legendsofhockey.net:8080/LegendsOfHockey/jsp/SearchPlayer.jsp?player=14707 | archive-date = July 14, 2006 | url-status = dead }}</ref>\n|}\n\n===X===\n\n===Y===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- align=left\n! style=\"width:20%;\"|Name\n! style=\"width:20%;\"|Occupation\n! style=\"width:60%;\"|Notes\n! style=\"width:20%;\"|Ref\n|-\n|[[Dylan Yeo]]\n|Hockey player||Currently plays for the [[Schwenninger Wild Wings]] in the [[Deutsche Eishockey Liga]]||<ref>{{cite web | title = Dylan Yeo hockey statistics and profile at hockeydb.com | work=| publisher=HockeyDB.com| url = http://www.hockeydb.com/ihdb/stats/pdisplay.php?pid=73510| accessdate = February 14, 2017}}</ref>\n|}\n\n===Z===\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Lists of people by city or town in Canada|Prince Albert]]\n[[Category:Lists of people from Saskatchewan]]\n[[Category:People from Prince Albert, Saskatchewan|*]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Prince Albert, Saskatchewan|*]]\n[[Category:Mayors of Prince Albert, Saskatchewan|*]]\n", "name_user": "G\u00fcnniX", "label": "safe", "comment": "https", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_people_from_Prince_Albert"}
{"title_page": "Richard Huckle", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=February 2020}}\n{{short description|British convicted sex offender}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Richard Huckleberry\n| image              = Richardhucklemugshot.jpg\n| caption            = Huckle's mugshot\n| image_size         = 220px\n|birth_name=Richard William Huckle\n| birth_place        = {{Nowrap|[[Ashford, Kent]], UK}}\n| death_place        = [[HM Prison Full Sutton|HMP Full Sutton]], East Riding of Yorkshire, UK\n| death_date         = {{death date and age|df=y|2019|10|13|1986|05|14}}\n| death_cause        = [[Strangulation]], [[stab wound]]\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date|df=y|1986|05|14}}\n| criminal_charge    = Convicted of 71 counts of serious sexual assault against children ranging from 6 months to 12 years old. The charges include:\n* 14 counts of rape of a child under the age of 12\n* 5 counts of digital penetration of a child under the age of 12\n* 31 counts of sexual assault against a child under the age of 12\n* 6 counts of grooming a child\n* 13 counts of taking/making indecent images of children related to the 20,000 images on his laptop\n* 1 count of advertising indecent images of children\n* 1 count of arranging or facilitating child sex offences.\nA further 20 offences [[lie on file|lay on file]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Prolific paedophile Richard Huckle facing life in prison for raping and abusing dozens of children.|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/crime/prolific-paedophile-richard-huckle-facing-life-in-prison-for-raping-and-abusing-dozens-of-children-a3261446.html|work=[[London Evening Standard]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref>\n| criminal_penalty   = 22 life sentences with a minimum term of 25 years.<ref name=skynewsresultofsentencing>{{cite news|title=Prolific Paedophile Gets 22 Life Sentences.|url=http://news.sky.com/story/1707642/prolific-paedophile-gets-22-life-sentences|publisher=[[Sky News]]|date=6 June 2016}}</ref>\n| criminal_status    = Died in prison\n| education = [[The Harvey Grammar School]], [[South Kent College]], [[Kuala Lumpur Metropolitan University College]]\n}}\n\n'''Richard William Huckle''' (14 May 1986 \u2013 13 October 2019) was a convicted British serial [[sex offender]]. He was arrested by Britain's [[National Crime Agency]] after a tip-off from Australian Police and convicted of 71 counts of serious sexual assaults against children while posing as a teacher, photographer and supposed [[Christians|Christian]] in Malaysia.<ref>{{cite news|title=Richard Huckle filmed himself abusing children and shared videos and pictures with fellow paedophiles on the Dark Web.|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160601231739/http://news.sky.com/story/1705318/prolific-paedophile-raped-babies-and-toddlers|publisher=[[Sky News]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nHuckle has been described as one of Britain's worst ever [[paedophile]]s, although he was only 28 years old at the time of his arrest.<ref name=TelegraphBritainsWorst>{{cite news|title=Britain's worst paedophile Richard Huckle who targeted poverty-stricken children faces life in prison after admitting scores of offences|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/06/01/britains-worst-paedophile-who-targeted-poverty-stricken-children/|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref><ref name=2harecourtstatement>{{cite web|url=http://www.2harecourt.com/2016/06/03/brian-oneill-qc-prosecutes-britains-worst-ever-paedophile/|title=Brian O\u2019Neill QC prosecutes \u2018Britain's worst ever paedophile\u2019- London Barristers Chambers|date=3 June 2016|website=2harecourt.com|accessdate=9 June 2016}}</ref><ref name=skynewsjune3prosecution>{{cite news|title=Paedophile Huckle Blames Abuse On 'Immaturity'|url=http://news.sky.com/story/1706394/paedophile-huckle-blames-abuse-on-immaturity|publisher=[[Sky News]]|date=3 June 2016}}</ref> On 6 June 2016, he was given 22 life sentences with a minimum prison term of 25 years before being eligible to apply for parole.<ref name=skynewsresultofsentencing />\n\nOn 13 October 2019, Huckle was stabbed to death in his cell at [[HMP Full Sutton]].<ref name=\"guardian-death\">{{cite news|last=Siddique|first=Haroon|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2019/oct/14/paedophile-richard-huckle-found-dead-in-prison|title=Paedophile Richard Huckle 'murdered' in prison|work=The Guardian|date=14 October 2019|access-date=23 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nHuckle was born into a middle-class family in [[Ashford, Kent|Ashford]], Kent, on 14 May 1986.{{cn|date=October 2019}} He was educated at [[the Harvey Grammar School]], [[Folkestone]], where he was described as \"a bit of a loner, but nothing out of the ordinary\" by friends.{{cn|date=October 2019}} At the age of 16, he took part in a month-long expedition to visit a school in [[Namibia]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Huckle Tried To Cash in On Child Abuse Pics|url=http://news.sky.com/story/1705161/huckle-tried-to-cash-in-on-child-abuse-pics|publisher=[[Sky News]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref> before leaving the Harvey Grammar School to study at the nearby [[South Kent College]].{{cn|date=March 2020}}\n\nHuckle was a regular worshipper at Ashford Baptist Church, where he was described as a quiet man.<ref>{{cite news|title=Richard Huckle's church minister reveals all on paedophile|url=http://www.folkestoneherald.co.uk/Richard-Huckle-s-church-minister-reveals/story-29352228-detail/story.html|publisher=Folkestone Herald ([[KM Group]])|date=2 June 2016}}</ref> He was also a member of a church in London, which he continued to attend up until the time of his re-arrest in January 2015.<ref name=skynewsvideo>{{cite news|title=Richard Huckle : Portrait of a paedophile|url=http://news.sky.com/video/1705530/huckle-portrait-of-a-paedophile|publisher=[[Sky News]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref> His pastor said in an interview of a series in \"Undercover Asia\" that he rarely came to church unless to see children.{{fact|date=March 2020}}\n\n== Time in Malaysia ==\nAfter leaving education, Huckle spent a gap year in [[Malaysia]] from 2005 to 2006.<ref>{{cite news|title=Richard Huckle one of UK's worst ever paedophiles|url=http://www.dover-express.co.uk/Richard-Huckle-UK-s-worst-paedophiles/story-29348170-detail/story.html|publisher=Dover Express ([[KM Group]])|date=2 June 2016}}</ref> He returned regularly, helping out at local churches and among local communities, before moving there permanently in 2010.{{citation needed|date=September 2016}}\n\nHuckle enrolled onto a short [[CELTA]] (Certificate in English Language Teaching to Adults) course with the [[British Council]]<ref name=smith2008>{{cite news|title=Statement on the Richard Huckle Case|url=https://www.britishcouncil.org/organisation/press/british-council-statement-richard-huckle-case|publisher=[[British Council]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref> before starting work as a freelance photographer in local communities around [[Kuala Lumpur]]. Hoping to further his career and status within the community,<ref>{{cite news|title=Paedophile who bragged about horrific sex crimes on 'dark web' facing life|url=http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/news/uk/paedophile-who-bragged-about-horrific-sex-crimes-on-dark-web-facing-life-34765029.html|work=[[The Belfast Telegraph]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref> he also enrolled onto an information technology (IT) study course at [[Kuala Lumpur Metropolitan University College]]. He did not complete his studies.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2016/06/03/he-wasnt-a-teacher-says-british-council|title=He wasn't a teacher, says British Council |work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]|location=Malaysia|date=3 June 2016|accessdate=31 December 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn addition to Malaysia, where all of the crimes he was convicted of occurred, and [[Cambodia]], which was also mentioned in the trial, Huckle travelled extensively around south-east Asia to countries including Singapore, [[Laos]] and [[India]].{{cn|date=October 2019}} It has been revealed that, while in India, he persuaded a pastor to invite him to an orphanage in [[Bangalore]] to take photos and make videos with the children, posing as a teacher to gain trust.{{cn|date=March 2020}}\n\n== Sexual offences ==\n\n=== Initial arrest ===\nOn 19 December 2014, Huckle was arrested by officers from Britain's [[National Crime Agency]] at London's [[Gatwick Airport]] and questioned on suspicion of serious offences against children.<ref name=howhucklecaught>{{cite news|title=How child abuser Richard Huckle was caught|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-36437856|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref> His arrest followed an earlier tip-off from [[Task Force Argos]], a highly specialised branch of Australia's [[Queensland Police Service]] responsible for the investigation of on-line child exploitation and abuse. Huckle initially refused to answer officers' questions and was bailed under the condition that he stay at his parents' house, while his camera, laptop and computer [[hard drives]] were seized.{{citation needed|date=September 2016}}\n\n=== Background of arrest ===\nPolice officers from Task Force Argos had been aware of a network of paedophiles operating on a [[dark web]] network called The Love Zone (TLZ). They noticed one member who always made posts using the unusual greeting \"hiyas\" and had a distinctive freckle on one of his fingers.<ref name=howhucklecaught /> Officers used the social media and chat rooms to track down the individual, eventually finding a Facebook page that appeared to be a match. The profile was fake but photos of a vehicle led police to Shannon McCoole, a care worker from Adelaide. A warrant was issued for the arrest of McCoole. Upon entering his house, police discovered that McCoole was online and running his dark website at the time.<ref name=howhucklecaught />\n\nPolice assumed the identity of McCoole and ran his site to catch other paedophiles. In doing so, police rescued 85 children from ongoing abuse and arrested hundreds.<ref>{{cite news|url = https://www.theguardian.com/society/2016/jul/13/shining-a-light-on-the-dark-web-how-the-police-ended-up-running-a-paedophile-site|date = 13 July 2016|accessdate = 13 July 2016|title = The takeover: how police ended up running a paedophile site|last = Safi|first = M.|newspaper = [[The Guardian]]}}</ref> One member that stood out was Huckle, due to the number of children he had abused and the attitude of his posts. After discovering his real identity, they learned that he was due to return to the United Kingdom to spend Christmas with his family and immediately alerted the National Crime Agency. He was arrested at Gatwick airport on 19 December 2014.<ref>{{cite news|title=How \u2018Britain's worst paedophile\u2019 Richard Huckle was caught|url=http://metro.co.uk/2016/06/02/how-britains-worst-paedophile-richard-huckle-was-caught-5920818/|publisher=[[Metro (British Newspaper)|Metro]]|date=2 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Family confession and re-arrest===\n\n{{refimprove section|date=October 2019}}\n\nHuckle had been granted bail under the conditions that he live at his parents' address whilst investigations were in progress. Huckle had no criminal record and was in no positions of responsibility concerning minors. The police therefore after interviewing him released him temporarily, as it would take time to analyse and retrieve evidence from seized computer equipment. In his initial police interview, Huckle made [[no comment]] throughout. When out on bail, he was confronted by his parents about the allegations, to which he claimed his innocence. Huckle later admitted to the allegations, at which point his parents refused to allow him to remain in the house and he returned to police custody.<ref name=\"kentonline\" />\n\n=== Remand and trial ===\n\nAfter leaving his parents' house Huckle was re-arrested and charged with 91 counts including creation and possession of child pornography, rape of a child under the age of 12, [[digital penetration]], child abuse, and facilitating the commission of child sexual offences by creating a paedophile manual. He was denied bail by the police and remanded to court where his latest application for bail was also denied, Huckle was now in prison custody, initially at [[HMP Lewes]] before, due to the severity of the charges, being transferred to [[HMP Belmarsh]] in London to await trial.<ref>{{cite news|title=Paedophile's Parents Begged Police To Take Him|url=http://news.sky.com/story/1705800/paedophiles-parents-begged-police-to-take-him|publisher=[[Sky News]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nAt an initial hearing at the [[Old Bailey]], in January 2016, Huckle pleaded not guilty to all 91 charges,<ref>{{cite news|title=Paedophile's Parents Begged Police To Take Him|url=http://www.itv.com/news/2016-06-01/british-paedophile-who-abused-up-to-200-victims-set-to-spend-rest-of-life-behind-bars/|publisher=[[ITV (TV network)|ITV]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref> which took over an hour to read in court, and prosecutors started to prepare three separate trials as they did not believe a jury should be subjected to all of the graphic evidence that would be presented in a single trial.<ref>{{cite news|title=Prolific Paedophile Raped Babies And Toddlers|url=http://news.sky.com/story/1705318/prolific-paedophile-raped-babies-and-toddlers|publisher=[[Sky News]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref> In April, during a preliminary trial hearing, Huckle pleaded guilty to 71 of the 91 charges he was facing after a request to watch all of the evidence against him in court.<ref name=TelegraphBritainsWorst /> As a result of his confession, prosecutors decided not to pursue a prosecution against the remaining 20 charges, and asked that they [[lie on file]], to spare a jury the horror of having to watch graphic images and videos of child abuse since the 71 charges which Huckle admitted to would be sufficient for a lengthy sentence.{{citation needed|date=September 2016}}\n\nDuring the hearings, the full scale of Huckle's crimes became apparent for the first time. The prosecution, led by Brian O'Neill QC,<ref name=2harecourtstatement /> showed evidence of a long line of crimes that started during Huckle's gap year in 2006 and continued for eight to nine years until he was apprehended in 2014. They included rape of children under the age of 12, possession and distribution of child pornography, creation of child pornography, child abuse, creating a paedophile manual entitled \"Paedophiles And Poverty: Child Lover Guide\", digital penetration of a child under the age of 12, and raising money for his activities via a crowd-funding website.<ref>{{cite news|title=Richard Huckle: Paedophile faces multiple life sentences for abusing \u2018up to 200 children\u2019 in Malaysia|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/crime/richard-huckle-paedophile-faces-multiple-life-sentences-at-old-bailey-for-abusing-children-in-a7060306.html|work=[[The Independent]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref> His victims ranged in age from 6 months to 12 years old; one was abused while wearing a [[Diaper|nappy]], and another was abused for a number of years between the ages of 5 and 12. Huckle belonged to a website called The Love Zone on the dark web, which is obscured from general discovery and only accessible by anonymised means. On the site, he shared photos of his crimes with other members.<ref>{{cite news|title=Britain's worst paedophile faces 22 life sentences for abusing 200 children in Malaysia|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/richard-huckle-britains-worst-paedophile-faces-22-life-sentences-abusing-200-children-malaysia-1563195|work=[[International Business Times]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref> He boasted about his crimes to other paedophiles, posting such comments as \"Hit the jackpot, a three-year-old girl as loyal to me as my dog and nobody seemed to care\" and \"impoverished kids are definitely much easier to seduce than middle-class kids\".<ref>{{cite news|title=Richard Huckle, 'Britain's worst pedophile', facing life in jail|url=http://www.9news.com.au/world/2016/06/02/13/55/richard-huckle-britains-worst-pedophile-facing-life-in-jail|publisher=[[Nine News]]|date=2 June 2016}}</ref> In total, prosecutors unveiled 29 victims and over 20,000 photos, but believe there could be up to 200 victims all over Southeast Asia and thousands more photos in encrypted areas of Huckle's laptop, which authorities have so far{{when|date=October 2019}} been unable to access.<ref name=guardianthrewout>{{cite news|title=Richard Huckle's parents 'threw him out when he admitted child abuse'|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2016/jun/02/richard-huckle-parents-threw-him-out-court-told|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref> The vast majority of child abuse on his laptop was never recovered as he refused to help police retrieve the encrypted data.<ref>https://www.kentlive.news/news/kent-news/bbc-documentary-richard-huckle-tell-526448</ref>\n\nThe hearings revealed some of the stratagems Huckle employed to procure victims, such as taking children out on day trips from orphanages and escorting them home from their own birthday party. Huckle had even talked about marrying one of his young victims so that he could set up a foster home and abuse \"a cycle of children\" who would pass through his home and turn paedophilia into a full-time job.<ref name=guardianthrewout /> Huckle also created a ledger of his abuses and where he scored the scale of abuse each victim suffered.<ref name=\"kentonline\">{{cite news|title=Paedophile Richard Huckle facing life in jail|url=http://www.kentonline.co.uk/ashford/news/prolific-paedophile-96746/|publisher=Kent Online ([[KM Group]])|date=1 June 2016}}</ref> It was from this ledger that the estimated number of children abused, 200, was derived, although so far authorities have only discovered photographic evidence of the abuse of 29 children due to Huckle refusing to give officers the passwords for encrypted areas of his hard drives.\n\n=== Extraterritorial jurisdiction ===\nHuckle was prosecuted under Section 72 of the [[Sexual Offences Act 2003]], which allows British nationals to be tried and convicted in the United Kingdom for child sex crimes committed while overseas in an effort to prevent [[child sex tourism]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2003/42/section/72|title=Sexual Offences Act 2003|publisher=Government of the United Kingdom|accessdate=9 June 2016}}</ref> a stratagem known as [[extraterritorial jurisdiction]] and a move welcomed by child protection charities.<ref name=TelegraphBritainsWorst /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ecpat.org.uk/media/wake-call-needed-over-abuse-children-abroad-ecpat-uk-warns|title=Wake-up call needed over abuse of children abroad, ECPAT UK warns|website=Ecpat.org.uk|accessdate=9 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nIt is a rarely used section of the Act: while no official tally is kept, it is believed{{by whom|date=October 2019}} that Huckle is only the seventh person to be prosecuted under the measure, and that his crimes are the most serious to be prosecuted under it.<ref name=skynewsvideo /><ref name=sentencingnewsyoutube>{{cite news|title=Sky news live broadcast after sentencing of Richard Huckle (uploaded to YouTube by a 3rd party)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=08fsUs-GWig|publisher=[[Sky News]]|date=6 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Sentencing ==\nHuckle's sentencing hearing began at the Old Bailey on 1 June 2016 and lasted until 3 June 2016, with the sentence itself being passed on 6 June 2016. At the start of the hearing, the judge stated that Huckle should expect to go to prison for a very long time, as he was considering multiple life sentences due to the gravity of the offences committed.<ref>{{cite news|title=Paedophile Richard Huckle, Who Targeted Poor Malaysian Children, Faces Life in Prison|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/paedophile-richard-huckle-targeted-poor-malaysian-children-faces-life-in-prison_uk_574f35a9e4b040e3e818ea49|work=[[HuffPost]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nDuring the sentencing hearing, Huckle's lawyer, Philip Sapsford QC, read a statement from Huckle where he blamed his crimes on his immaturity:<ref name=skynewsjune3prosecution />\n\n{{quote|I really understand and acknowledge the true scale of damage it caused to the Malaysian community. I had hoped to escape this mundane life of solitude in the UK yet was overwhelmed by the attention I received in Malaysia. I completely misjudged the affections I received from these children. My low self-esteem and lack of confidence with women was no excuse for me to use these children as an outlet. I am open and eager to rehabilitate from this offending behaviour. I don't want to become a martyr to sex tourism in Malaysia. This was all my doing as a consequence of my immaturity and I'm truly remorseful.|author=Richard Huckle|source=A statement read on his behalf by his defence team.<ref name=skynewsjune3prosecution /><ref>{{cite news|title=Richard Huckle 'deeply remorseful' for child sex abuse, court told|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/jun/03/richard-huckle-deeply-remorseful-for-child-abuse-crimes-court-told|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=3 June 2016}}</ref> }}\nSapsford continued by asking the judge to take into consideration his client's young age, his claims of remorse, and the fact that he had no previous convictions. He also quoted from a psychiatric report that said Huckle had limited sexual experience with women and suffered depression as a teenager. He also stated that, despite the mitigating circumstances, this is the most extensive case of child sex crimes that he has ever been involved in.<ref name=skynewsjune3prosecution />\n\nIt was also noted during the hearing, in a statement made by the prosecution, how convictions were only sought against crimes for which there was complete photographic evidence. It was noted how Huckle's ledger contained details of 200 children that had been abused but that they have been unable to access certain encrypted sections of his hard drive to obtain evidence.<ref name=skynewsjune3prosecution />\n\nAt the Old Bailey on 6 June 2016, Judge Peter Rook QC sentenced Huckle to life imprisonment on 22 counts with a minimum prison term of 25 years before being eligible to apply for [[Parole Board for England and Wales|parole]].<ref name=sentencingnewsyoutube /> Before passing down the sentence, the judge stated that Huckle carried out a campaign of rape and was driven by his own sexual gratification:<ref name=skynewsresultofsentencing /><ref>{{cite news|title=Richard Huckle given 22 life sentences for abusing Malaysian children|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2016/jun/06/richard-huckle-given-23-life-sentences-for-abusing-malaysian-children|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=6 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n{{quote|You have pleaded guilty to as many as 71 sexual offences. It is very rare indeed that a judge has to sentence sexual offending by one person on such a scale as this. In my view, you may well harbour feelings of regret but there is no feeling of genuine remorse in this case.|author=Judge Peter Rook QC|source=6 June 2016}}\n\n== Aftermath and criticism ==\nThe National Crime Agency received criticism from the [[Government of Malaysia|Malaysian Government]], as well as a number of child protection charities in Malaysia, for their handling of the case. Officers from the NCA travelled to Malaysia to engage local charities, who performed child protection workshops in the community where Huckle lived, but they were kept in the dark about the gravity of his crimes. The Malaysian Government stated that they would like further details of the victims so they can offer counselling.<ref>{{cite news|title=Women's ministry to probe Huckle case, sets up info hotline|url=http://www.themalaymailonline.com/malaysia/article/womens-ministry-to-probe-huckle-case-sets-up-info-hotline|work=[[The Malay Mail]]|date=2 June 2016}}</ref> On 4 June 2016, the [[Attorney General of Malaysia]], Tan [[Mohamed Apandi Ali]], stated that he was in the process of contacting his counterpart in the UK, and the British High Commissioner in [[Kuala Lumpur]], to obtain information about the case, which would help his investigation into the crimes and his efforts to help Huckle's victims.<ref>{{cite news|title=In bid for information, AG to contact British counterpart on Richard Huckle|url=http://www.themalaymailonline.com/malaysia/article/in-bid-for-information-ag-to-contact-british-counterpart-on-richard-huckle|work=[[The Malay Mail]]|date=4 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe National Crime Agency responded to the comments from the Malaysian authorities, stating that they revealed enough details to be able to help the charities but were unable to provide full details until the prosecution was completed. For the same reason, severe media restrictions were put in place, which prevented anybody from reporting the story until the British Government had taken steps to ensure that all of Huckle's material had been taken down and that steps had been taken to protect his victims from other predators.<ref>{{cite news|title=UK paedophile admits string of sex attacks on Malaysian children|url=http://www.news.com.au/world/asia/uk-paedophile-admits-string-of-sex-attacks-on-malaysian-children/news-story/85d11fecb09522879f41f15c210875b2|publisher=[[news.com.au]]|date=2 June 2016}}</ref> On 6 June 2016, however, the National Crime Agency referred itself to the police watchdog, the [[Independent Police Complaints Commission]], due to the fact that they were aware of Huckle's continued attendance at two churches in the UK up until the time of his re-arrest in January 2015 but did not contact them until sentencing had already begun. The IPCC will look into whether the NCA had acted appropriately and whether more could have been done to determine whether Huckle abused any children in the UK through his relationship with the churches.<ref name=sentencingnewsyoutube /><ref>{{cite news|title=Britain's worst paedophile Richard Huckle jailed for life for abusing up to 200 children in Malaysia|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/uk-news/britains-worst-paedophile-richard-huckle-8122982|work=[[Daily Mirror]]|date=6 June 2016}}</ref>{{Update inline|date=February 2018}}\n\nThe British Council issued a statement saying that they had reviewed their dealings with Huckle:\n\n{{quote|Richard Huckle completed a Certificate in English Language Teaching to Adults (CELTA) course in 2008 which provides training to individuals to teach adult learners. Following the course, we have no records to indicate he was ever engaged as a teacher in Malaysia with us, either for adult students or children.|author=British Council Press Office|source=a statement issued 1 June 2016<ref name=smith2008 />}}\n\nThey also stated that procedures would be reviewed, but that pre-employment checks are the responsibility of future employers not their education provider.<ref name=smith2008 />{{Update inline|date=February 2018}}\n\nAfter the gravity of Huckle's crimes became known, the Malaysian Government set up a telephone hotline for people to call if they have any information about Huckle or if they were abused themselves.<ref>{{cite news|title=Hotline set up for info on British paedophile Richard Huckle|url=http://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2016/06/02/hotline-set-up-for-info-on-british-paedophile-richard-huckle/|work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]|location=Malaysia|date=2 June 2016}}</ref> The Malaysian Prime Minister, [[Najib Razak]], added that he was angered and saddened by Huckle's sexual violation of Malaysian children and called for all parties involved to ensure that children are not exposed to situations where irresponsible people can take advantage of them.<ref>{{cite news|title=Najib: Heed lessons from Richard Huckle case|url=http://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2016/06/08/najib-heed-lessons-from-richard-huckle-case/|work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]|location=Malaysia|date=8 June 2016}}</ref> In August 2016, in response to the criticism following the Huckle case, Najib Razak announced that a special task force had been set up to investigate how Malaysia's child protection laws could be redrafted to take into account the new ways that child sexual predators such as Huckle were preying on Malaysian children,<ref>{{cite news|title=PMO sets up task force to review child protection laws|url=http://www.themalaymailonline.com/malaysia/article/pmo-sets-up-task-force-to-review-child-protection-laws|work=[[The Malay Mail]]|date=25 August 2016}}</ref> with the aim of having a new version ready by the end of the year.{{Update inline|date=February 2018}}\n\nFollowing the discovery of Huckle's crimes, the Malaysian Government came under fire from child protection charities for their lack of laws against child abuse and child pornography. James Nayagam, chairman of Suriana Welfare Society for Children, was particularly critical of his government's relaxed nature in dealing with such crimes:<ref name=starmalaysiacriticism>{{cite news|title=Have laws on child porn or another Richard Huckle|url=http://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2016/06/03/have-laws-on-child-pornography-or-another-richard-huckle/|work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]|location=Malaysia|date=3 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n{{quote|Malaysia should make child pornography and child sexual abuse a severe crime with heavy penalties. We should also issue a severe warning at the point of entering the country about our strong stance. Huckle got away with it. He knew the relaxed atmosphere in this country. We Asians fall head over heels with foreigners. He had people fall into his trap. But regardless of where people come from, we must have that check and balance.|author=James Nayagam|source=A newspaper article<ref name=starmalaysiacriticism />}}\n\nIn the article, Nayagam continued by pointing out that Section 292 of the Penal Code only deals with sale and distribution of obscene material.<ref name=starmalaysiacriticism />\n\nWhile the media in the UK were largely supportive of Huckle's sentencing, the Malaysian press widely stated that the punishment was not severe enough, with statements such as \"a thousand years is not enough\", \"We are horrified that the sex fiend [Huckle] will be eligible to appear before a parole board after 23 years\", and \"this monster could be out in 24 years\" appearing in the days after his sentence was announced.<ref>{{cite news|title=Malaysians say harsher sentence needed for Britain's 'worst paedophile' Richard Huckle|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/06/07/malaysians-say-harsher-sentence-needed-for-britains-worst-paedop/ |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=7 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=\u20181,000 years not enough\u2019 for jailed pedophile Richard Huckle \u2013 Malaysian media|url=https://www.rt.com/uk/345669-huckle-prison-malaysia-abuse/|publisher=[[RT (TV Network)|RT]]|date=7 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Death ==\n\nOn 13 October 2019, Huckle was found strangled and stabbed to death in his cell at [[HM Prison Full Sutton|Full Sutton]] prison, aged 33.<ref name=\"guardian-death\" /><ref>{{cite news |date= 14 October 2019 |title= Richard Huckle: Paedophile killed in prison 'strangled and stabbed' |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-50072903 |publisher= BBC News |access-date= 16 October 2019}}</ref> Another prisoner was charged with his murder in January 2020.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/amp/uk-england-humber-51239756|title=Richard Huckle jail killing: Inmate charged with murder|date=January 24, 2020|work=BBC News}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* \"[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sF9-r4JjRBw Richard Huckle stabbing: Portrait of a Paedophile]\" \u2013 [[Sky News]] documentary ([https://web.archive.org/web/20160606211554/https://news.sky.com/video/1705530/huckle-portrait-of-a-paedophile profile])\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Huckle, Richard}}\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:2019 deaths]]\n[[Category:21st-century English criminals]]\n[[Category:British people convicted of sexual assault]]\n[[Category:English people convicted of rape]]\n[[Category:Prisoners sentenced to life imprisonment by England and Wales]]\n[[Category:English Christians]]\n[[Category:English people convicted of child pornography offences]]\n[[Category:English people convicted of child sexual abuse]]\n[[Category:English photographers]]\n[[Category:English prisoners sentenced to life imprisonment]]\n[[Category:English sex offenders]]\n[[Category:English people who died in prison custody]]\n[[Category:English murder victims]]\n[[Category:British expatriates in Malaysia]]\n[[Category:Child grooming]]\n[[Category:Crime in Malaysia]]\n[[Category:Crime in Kuala Lumpur]]\n[[Category:Child sexual abuse scandals in religions]]\n[[Category:Deaths by stabbing in England]]\n[[Category:Teachers of English as a second or foreign language]]\n[[Category:Child pornography]]\n[[Category:People educated at The Harvey Grammar School]]\n[[Category:People murdered in England]]\n[[Category:Prisoners murdered in custody]]\n[[Category:Prisoners who died in England and Wales detention]]\n[[Category:Inmates of HM Prison Belmarsh]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=February 2020}}\n{{short description|British convicted sex offender}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Richard Huckle\n| image              = Richardhucklemugshot.jpg\n| caption            = Huckle's mugshot\n| image_size         = 220px\n|birth_name=Richard William Huckle\n| birth_place        = {{Nowrap|[[Ashford, Kent]], UK}}\n| death_place        = [[HM Prison Full Sutton|HMP Full Sutton]], East Riding of Yorkshire, UK\n| death_date         = {{death date and age|df=y|2019|10|13|1986|05|14}}\n| death_cause        = [[Strangulation]], [[stab wound]]\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date|df=y|1986|05|14}}\n| criminal_charge    = Convicted of 71 counts of serious sexual assault against children ranging from 6 months to 12 years old. The charges include:\n* 14 counts of rape of a child under the age of 12\n* 5 counts of digital penetration of a child under the age of 12\n* 31 counts of sexual assault against a child under the age of 12\n* 6 counts of grooming a child\n* 13 counts of taking/making indecent images of children related to the 20,000 images on his laptop\n* 1 count of advertising indecent images of children\n* 1 count of arranging or facilitating child sex offences.\nA further 20 offences [[lie on file|lay on file]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Prolific paedophile Richard Huckle facing life in prison for raping and abusing dozens of children.|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/news/crime/prolific-paedophile-richard-huckle-facing-life-in-prison-for-raping-and-abusing-dozens-of-children-a3261446.html|work=[[London Evening Standard]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref>\n| criminal_penalty   = 22 life sentences with a minimum term of 25 years.<ref name=skynewsresultofsentencing>{{cite news|title=Prolific Paedophile Gets 22 Life Sentences.|url=http://news.sky.com/story/1707642/prolific-paedophile-gets-22-life-sentences|publisher=[[Sky News]]|date=6 June 2016}}</ref>\n| criminal_status    = Died in prison\n| education = [[The Harvey Grammar School]], [[South Kent College]], [[Kuala Lumpur Metropolitan University College]]\n}}\n\n'''Richard William Huckle''' (14 May 1986 \u2013 13 October 2019) was a convicted British serial [[sex offender]]. He was arrested by Britain's [[National Crime Agency]] after a tip-off from Australian Police and convicted of 71 counts of serious sexual assaults against children while posing as a teacher, photographer and supposed [[Christians|Christian]] in Malaysia.<ref>{{cite news|title=Richard Huckle filmed himself abusing children and shared videos and pictures with fellow paedophiles on the Dark Web.|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160601231739/http://news.sky.com/story/1705318/prolific-paedophile-raped-babies-and-toddlers|publisher=[[Sky News]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nHuckle has been described as one of Britain's worst ever [[paedophile]]s, although he was only 28 years old at the time of his arrest.<ref name=TelegraphBritainsWorst>{{cite news|title=Britain's worst paedophile Richard Huckle who targeted poverty-stricken children faces life in prison after admitting scores of offences|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/06/01/britains-worst-paedophile-who-targeted-poverty-stricken-children/|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref><ref name=2harecourtstatement>{{cite web|url=http://www.2harecourt.com/2016/06/03/brian-oneill-qc-prosecutes-britains-worst-ever-paedophile/|title=Brian O\u2019Neill QC prosecutes \u2018Britain's worst ever paedophile\u2019- London Barristers Chambers|date=3 June 2016|website=2harecourt.com|accessdate=9 June 2016}}</ref><ref name=skynewsjune3prosecution>{{cite news|title=Paedophile Huckle Blames Abuse On 'Immaturity'|url=http://news.sky.com/story/1706394/paedophile-huckle-blames-abuse-on-immaturity|publisher=[[Sky News]]|date=3 June 2016}}</ref> On 6 June 2016, he was given 22 life sentences with a minimum prison term of 25 years before being eligible to apply for parole.<ref name=skynewsresultofsentencing />\n\nOn 13 October 2019, Huckle was stabbed to death in his cell at [[HMP Full Sutton]].<ref name=\"guardian-death\">{{cite news|last=Siddique|first=Haroon|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2019/oct/14/paedophile-richard-huckle-found-dead-in-prison|title=Paedophile Richard Huckle 'murdered' in prison|work=The Guardian|date=14 October 2019|access-date=23 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nHuckle was born into a middle-class family in [[Ashford, Kent|Ashford]], Kent, on 14 May 1986.{{cn|date=October 2019}} He was educated at [[the Harvey Grammar School]], [[Folkestone]], where he was described as \"a bit of a loner, but nothing out of the ordinary\" by friends.{{cn|date=October 2019}} At the age of 16, he took part in a month-long expedition to visit a school in [[Namibia]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Huckle Tried To Cash in On Child Abuse Pics|url=http://news.sky.com/story/1705161/huckle-tried-to-cash-in-on-child-abuse-pics|publisher=[[Sky News]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref> before leaving the Harvey Grammar School to study at the nearby [[South Kent College]].{{cn|date=March 2020}}\n\nHuckle was a regular worshipper at Ashford Baptist Church, where he was described as a quiet man.<ref>{{cite news|title=Richard Huckle's church minister reveals all on paedophile|url=http://www.folkestoneherald.co.uk/Richard-Huckle-s-church-minister-reveals/story-29352228-detail/story.html|publisher=Folkestone Herald ([[KM Group]])|date=2 June 2016}}</ref> He was also a member of a church in London, which he continued to attend up until the time of his re-arrest in January 2015.<ref name=skynewsvideo>{{cite news|title=Richard Huckle : Portrait of a paedophile|url=http://news.sky.com/video/1705530/huckle-portrait-of-a-paedophile|publisher=[[Sky News]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref> His pastor said in an interview of a series in \"Undercover Asia\" that he rarely came to church unless to see children.{{fact|date=March 2020}}\n\n== Time in Malaysia ==\nAfter leaving education, Huckle spent a gap year in [[Malaysia]] from 2005 to 2006.<ref>{{cite news|title=Richard Huckle one of UK's worst ever paedophiles|url=http://www.dover-express.co.uk/Richard-Huckle-UK-s-worst-paedophiles/story-29348170-detail/story.html|publisher=Dover Express ([[KM Group]])|date=2 June 2016}}</ref> He returned regularly, helping out at local churches and among local communities, before moving there permanently in 2010.{{citation needed|date=September 2016}}\n\nHuckle enrolled onto a short [[CELTA]] (Certificate in English Language Teaching to Adults) course with the [[British Council]]<ref name=smith2008>{{cite news|title=Statement on the Richard Huckle Case|url=https://www.britishcouncil.org/organisation/press/british-council-statement-richard-huckle-case|publisher=[[British Council]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref> before starting work as a freelance photographer in local communities around [[Kuala Lumpur]]. Hoping to further his career and status within the community,<ref>{{cite news|title=Paedophile who bragged about horrific sex crimes on 'dark web' facing life|url=http://www.belfasttelegraph.co.uk/news/uk/paedophile-who-bragged-about-horrific-sex-crimes-on-dark-web-facing-life-34765029.html|work=[[The Belfast Telegraph]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref> he also enrolled onto an information technology (IT) study course at [[Kuala Lumpur Metropolitan University College]]. He did not complete his studies.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2016/06/03/he-wasnt-a-teacher-says-british-council|title=He wasn't a teacher, says British Council |work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]|location=Malaysia|date=3 June 2016|accessdate=31 December 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn addition to Malaysia, where all of the crimes he was convicted of occurred, and [[Cambodia]], which was also mentioned in the trial, Huckle travelled extensively around south-east Asia to countries including Singapore, [[Laos]] and [[India]].{{cn|date=October 2019}} It has been revealed that, while in India, he persuaded a pastor to invite him to an orphanage in [[Bangalore]] to take photos and make videos with the children, posing as a teacher to gain trust.{{cn|date=March 2020}}\n\n== Sexual offences ==\n\n=== Initial arrest ===\nOn 19 December 2014, Huckle was arrested by officers from Britain's [[National Crime Agency]] at London's [[Gatwick Airport]] and questioned on suspicion of serious offences against children.<ref name=howhucklecaught>{{cite news|title=How child abuser Richard Huckle was caught|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-36437856|publisher=[[BBC]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref> His arrest followed an earlier tip-off from [[Task Force Argos]], a highly specialised branch of Australia's [[Queensland Police Service]] responsible for the investigation of on-line child exploitation and abuse. Huckle initially refused to answer officers' questions and was bailed under the condition that he stay at his parents' house, while his camera, laptop and computer [[hard drives]] were seized.{{citation needed|date=September 2016}}\n\n=== Background of arrest ===\nPolice officers from Task Force Argos had been aware of a network of paedophiles operating on a [[dark web]] network called The Love Zone (TLZ). They noticed one member who always made posts using the unusual greeting \"hiyas\" and had a distinctive freckle on one of his fingers.<ref name=howhucklecaught /> Officers used the social media and chat rooms to track down the individual, eventually finding a Facebook page that appeared to be a match. The profile was fake but photos of a vehicle led police to Shannon McCoole, a care worker from Adelaide. A warrant was issued for the arrest of McCoole. Upon entering his house, police discovered that McCoole was online and running his dark website at the time.<ref name=howhucklecaught />\n\nPolice assumed the identity of McCoole and ran his site to catch other paedophiles. In doing so, police rescued 85 children from ongoing abuse and arrested hundreds.<ref>{{cite news|url = https://www.theguardian.com/society/2016/jul/13/shining-a-light-on-the-dark-web-how-the-police-ended-up-running-a-paedophile-site|date = 13 July 2016|accessdate = 13 July 2016|title = The takeover: how police ended up running a paedophile site|last = Safi|first = M.|newspaper = [[The Guardian]]}}</ref> One member that stood out was Huckle, due to the number of children he had abused and the attitude of his posts. After discovering his real identity, they learned that he was due to return to the United Kingdom to spend Christmas with his family and immediately alerted the National Crime Agency. He was arrested at Gatwick airport on 19 December 2014.<ref>{{cite news|title=How \u2018Britain's worst paedophile\u2019 Richard Huckle was caught|url=http://metro.co.uk/2016/06/02/how-britains-worst-paedophile-richard-huckle-was-caught-5920818/|publisher=[[Metro (British Newspaper)|Metro]]|date=2 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Family confession and re-arrest===\n\n{{refimprove section|date=October 2019}}\n\nHuckle had been granted bail under the conditions that he live at his parents' address whilst investigations were in progress. Huckle had no criminal record and was in no positions of responsibility concerning minors. The police therefore after interviewing him released him temporarily, as it would take time to analyse and retrieve evidence from seized computer equipment. In his initial police interview, Huckle made [[no comment]] throughout. When out on bail, he was confronted by his parents about the allegations, to which he claimed his innocence. Huckle later admitted to the allegations, at which point his parents refused to allow him to remain in the house and he returned to police custody.<ref name=\"kentonline\" />\n\n=== Remand and trial ===\n\nAfter leaving his parents' house Huckle was re-arrested and charged with 91 counts including creation and possession of child pornography, rape of a child under the age of 12, [[digital penetration]], child abuse, and facilitating the commission of child sexual offences by creating a paedophile manual. He was denied bail by the police and remanded to court where his latest application for bail was also denied, Huckle was now in prison custody, initially at [[HMP Lewes]] before, due to the severity of the charges, being transferred to [[HMP Belmarsh]] in London to await trial.<ref>{{cite news|title=Paedophile's Parents Begged Police To Take Him|url=http://news.sky.com/story/1705800/paedophiles-parents-begged-police-to-take-him|publisher=[[Sky News]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nAt an initial hearing at the [[Old Bailey]], in January 2016, Huckle pleaded not guilty to all 91 charges,<ref>{{cite news|title=Paedophile's Parents Begged Police To Take Him|url=http://www.itv.com/news/2016-06-01/british-paedophile-who-abused-up-to-200-victims-set-to-spend-rest-of-life-behind-bars/|publisher=[[ITV (TV network)|ITV]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref> which took over an hour to read in court, and prosecutors started to prepare three separate trials as they did not believe a jury should be subjected to all of the graphic evidence that would be presented in a single trial.<ref>{{cite news|title=Prolific Paedophile Raped Babies And Toddlers|url=http://news.sky.com/story/1705318/prolific-paedophile-raped-babies-and-toddlers|publisher=[[Sky News]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref> In April, during a preliminary trial hearing, Huckle pleaded guilty to 71 of the 91 charges he was facing after a request to watch all of the evidence against him in court.<ref name=TelegraphBritainsWorst /> As a result of his confession, prosecutors decided not to pursue a prosecution against the remaining 20 charges, and asked that they [[lie on file]], to spare a jury the horror of having to watch graphic images and videos of child abuse since the 71 charges which Huckle admitted to would be sufficient for a lengthy sentence.{{citation needed|date=September 2016}}\n\nDuring the hearings, the full scale of Huckle's crimes became apparent for the first time. The prosecution, led by Brian O'Neill QC,<ref name=2harecourtstatement /> showed evidence of a long line of crimes that started during Huckle's gap year in 2006 and continued for eight to nine years until he was apprehended in 2014. They included rape of children under the age of 12, possession and distribution of child pornography, creation of child pornography, child abuse, creating a paedophile manual entitled \"Paedophiles And Poverty: Child Lover Guide\", digital penetration of a child under the age of 12, and raising money for his activities via a crowd-funding website.<ref>{{cite news|title=Richard Huckle: Paedophile faces multiple life sentences for abusing \u2018up to 200 children\u2019 in Malaysia|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/crime/richard-huckle-paedophile-faces-multiple-life-sentences-at-old-bailey-for-abusing-children-in-a7060306.html|work=[[The Independent]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref> His victims ranged in age from 6 months to 12 years old; one was abused while wearing a [[Diaper|nappy]], and another was abused for a number of years between the ages of 5 and 12. Huckle belonged to a website called The Love Zone on the dark web, which is obscured from general discovery and only accessible by anonymised means. On the site, he shared photos of his crimes with other members.<ref>{{cite news|title=Britain's worst paedophile faces 22 life sentences for abusing 200 children in Malaysia|url=http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/richard-huckle-britains-worst-paedophile-faces-22-life-sentences-abusing-200-children-malaysia-1563195|work=[[International Business Times]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref> He boasted about his crimes to other paedophiles, posting such comments as \"Hit the jackpot, a three-year-old girl as loyal to me as my dog and nobody seemed to care\" and \"impoverished kids are definitely much easier to seduce than middle-class kids\".<ref>{{cite news|title=Richard Huckle, 'Britain's worst pedophile', facing life in jail|url=http://www.9news.com.au/world/2016/06/02/13/55/richard-huckle-britains-worst-pedophile-facing-life-in-jail|publisher=[[Nine News]]|date=2 June 2016}}</ref> In total, prosecutors unveiled 29 victims and over 20,000 photos, but believe there could be up to 200 victims all over Southeast Asia and thousands more photos in encrypted areas of Huckle's laptop, which authorities have so far{{when|date=October 2019}} been unable to access.<ref name=guardianthrewout>{{cite news|title=Richard Huckle's parents 'threw him out when he admitted child abuse'|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2016/jun/02/richard-huckle-parents-threw-him-out-court-told|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref> The vast majority of child abuse on his laptop was never recovered as he refused to help police retrieve the encrypted data.<ref>https://www.kentlive.news/news/kent-news/bbc-documentary-richard-huckle-tell-526448</ref>\n\nThe hearings revealed some of the stratagems Huckle employed to procure victims, such as taking children out on day trips from orphanages and escorting them home from their own birthday party. Huckle had even talked about marrying one of his young victims so that he could set up a foster home and abuse \"a cycle of children\" who would pass through his home and turn paedophilia into a full-time job.<ref name=guardianthrewout /> Huckle also created a ledger of his abuses and where he scored the scale of abuse each victim suffered.<ref name=\"kentonline\">{{cite news|title=Paedophile Richard Huckle facing life in jail|url=http://www.kentonline.co.uk/ashford/news/prolific-paedophile-96746/|publisher=Kent Online ([[KM Group]])|date=1 June 2016}}</ref> It was from this ledger that the estimated number of children abused, 200, was derived, although so far authorities have only discovered photographic evidence of the abuse of 29 children due to Huckle refusing to give officers the passwords for encrypted areas of his hard drives.\n\n=== Extraterritorial jurisdiction ===\nHuckle was prosecuted under Section 72 of the [[Sexual Offences Act 2003]], which allows British nationals to be tried and convicted in the United Kingdom for child sex crimes committed while overseas in an effort to prevent [[child sex tourism]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2003/42/section/72|title=Sexual Offences Act 2003|publisher=Government of the United Kingdom|accessdate=9 June 2016}}</ref> a stratagem known as [[extraterritorial jurisdiction]] and a move welcomed by child protection charities.<ref name=TelegraphBritainsWorst /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ecpat.org.uk/media/wake-call-needed-over-abuse-children-abroad-ecpat-uk-warns|title=Wake-up call needed over abuse of children abroad, ECPAT UK warns|website=Ecpat.org.uk|accessdate=9 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nIt is a rarely used section of the Act: while no official tally is kept, it is believed{{by whom|date=October 2019}} that Huckle is only the seventh person to be prosecuted under the measure, and that his crimes are the most serious to be prosecuted under it.<ref name=skynewsvideo /><ref name=sentencingnewsyoutube>{{cite news|title=Sky news live broadcast after sentencing of Richard Huckle (uploaded to YouTube by a 3rd party)|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=08fsUs-GWig|publisher=[[Sky News]]|date=6 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Sentencing ==\nHuckle's sentencing hearing began at the Old Bailey on 1 June 2016 and lasted until 3 June 2016, with the sentence itself being passed on 6 June 2016. At the start of the hearing, the judge stated that Huckle should expect to go to prison for a very long time, as he was considering multiple life sentences due to the gravity of the offences committed.<ref>{{cite news|title=Paedophile Richard Huckle, Who Targeted Poor Malaysian Children, Faces Life in Prison|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/paedophile-richard-huckle-targeted-poor-malaysian-children-faces-life-in-prison_uk_574f35a9e4b040e3e818ea49|work=[[HuffPost]]|date=1 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nDuring the sentencing hearing, Huckle's lawyer, Philip Sapsford QC, read a statement from Huckle where he blamed his crimes on his immaturity:<ref name=skynewsjune3prosecution />\n\n{{quote|I really understand and acknowledge the true scale of damage it caused to the Malaysian community. I had hoped to escape this mundane life of solitude in the UK yet was overwhelmed by the attention I received in Malaysia. I completely misjudged the affections I received from these children. My low self-esteem and lack of confidence with women was no excuse for me to use these children as an outlet. I am open and eager to rehabilitate from this offending behaviour. I don't want to become a martyr to sex tourism in Malaysia. This was all my doing as a consequence of my immaturity and I'm truly remorseful.|author=Richard Huckle|source=A statement read on his behalf by his defence team.<ref name=skynewsjune3prosecution /><ref>{{cite news|title=Richard Huckle 'deeply remorseful' for child sex abuse, court told|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/jun/03/richard-huckle-deeply-remorseful-for-child-abuse-crimes-court-told|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=3 June 2016}}</ref> }}\nSapsford continued by asking the judge to take into consideration his client's young age, his claims of remorse, and the fact that he had no previous convictions. He also quoted from a psychiatric report that said Huckle had limited sexual experience with women and suffered depression as a teenager. He also stated that, despite the mitigating circumstances, this is the most extensive case of child sex crimes that he has ever been involved in.<ref name=skynewsjune3prosecution />\n\nIt was also noted during the hearing, in a statement made by the prosecution, how convictions were only sought against crimes for which there was complete photographic evidence. It was noted how Huckle's ledger contained details of 200 children that had been abused but that they have been unable to access certain encrypted sections of his hard drive to obtain evidence.<ref name=skynewsjune3prosecution />\n\nAt the Old Bailey on 6 June 2016, Judge Peter Rook QC sentenced Huckle to life imprisonment on 22 counts with a minimum prison term of 25 years before being eligible to apply for [[Parole Board for England and Wales|parole]].<ref name=sentencingnewsyoutube /> Before passing down the sentence, the judge stated that Huckle carried out a campaign of rape and was driven by his own sexual gratification:<ref name=skynewsresultofsentencing /><ref>{{cite news|title=Richard Huckle given 22 life sentences for abusing Malaysian children|url=https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2016/jun/06/richard-huckle-given-23-life-sentences-for-abusing-malaysian-children|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=6 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n{{quote|You have pleaded guilty to as many as 71 sexual offences. It is very rare indeed that a judge has to sentence sexual offending by one person on such a scale as this. In my view, you may well harbour feelings of regret but there is no feeling of genuine remorse in this case.|author=Judge Peter Rook QC|source=6 June 2016}}\n\n== Aftermath and criticism ==\nThe National Crime Agency received criticism from the [[Government of Malaysia|Malaysian Government]], as well as a number of child protection charities in Malaysia, for their handling of the case. Officers from the NCA travelled to Malaysia to engage local charities, who performed child protection workshops in the community where Huckle lived, but they were kept in the dark about the gravity of his crimes. The Malaysian Government stated that they would like further details of the victims so they can offer counselling.<ref>{{cite news|title=Women's ministry to probe Huckle case, sets up info hotline|url=http://www.themalaymailonline.com/malaysia/article/womens-ministry-to-probe-huckle-case-sets-up-info-hotline|work=[[The Malay Mail]]|date=2 June 2016}}</ref> On 4 June 2016, the [[Attorney General of Malaysia]], Tan [[Mohamed Apandi Ali]], stated that he was in the process of contacting his counterpart in the UK, and the British High Commissioner in [[Kuala Lumpur]], to obtain information about the case, which would help his investigation into the crimes and his efforts to help Huckle's victims.<ref>{{cite news|title=In bid for information, AG to contact British counterpart on Richard Huckle|url=http://www.themalaymailonline.com/malaysia/article/in-bid-for-information-ag-to-contact-british-counterpart-on-richard-huckle|work=[[The Malay Mail]]|date=4 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe National Crime Agency responded to the comments from the Malaysian authorities, stating that they revealed enough details to be able to help the charities but were unable to provide full details until the prosecution was completed. For the same reason, severe media restrictions were put in place, which prevented anybody from reporting the story until the British Government had taken steps to ensure that all of Huckle's material had been taken down and that steps had been taken to protect his victims from other predators.<ref>{{cite news|title=UK paedophile admits string of sex attacks on Malaysian children|url=http://www.news.com.au/world/asia/uk-paedophile-admits-string-of-sex-attacks-on-malaysian-children/news-story/85d11fecb09522879f41f15c210875b2|publisher=[[news.com.au]]|date=2 June 2016}}</ref> On 6 June 2016, however, the National Crime Agency referred itself to the police watchdog, the [[Independent Police Complaints Commission]], due to the fact that they were aware of Huckle's continued attendance at two churches in the UK up until the time of his re-arrest in January 2015 but did not contact them until sentencing had already begun. The IPCC will look into whether the NCA had acted appropriately and whether more could have been done to determine whether Huckle abused any children in the UK through his relationship with the churches.<ref name=sentencingnewsyoutube /><ref>{{cite news|title=Britain's worst paedophile Richard Huckle jailed for life for abusing up to 200 children in Malaysia|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/uk-news/britains-worst-paedophile-richard-huckle-8122982|work=[[Daily Mirror]]|date=6 June 2016}}</ref>{{Update inline|date=February 2018}}\n\nThe British Council issued a statement saying that they had reviewed their dealings with Huckle:\n\n{{quote|Richard Huckle completed a Certificate in English Language Teaching to Adults (CELTA) course in 2008 which provides training to individuals to teach adult learners. Following the course, we have no records to indicate he was ever engaged as a teacher in Malaysia with us, either for adult students or children.|author=British Council Press Office|source=a statement issued 1 June 2016<ref name=smith2008 />}}\n\nThey also stated that procedures would be reviewed, but that pre-employment checks are the responsibility of future employers not their education provider.<ref name=smith2008 />{{Update inline|date=February 2018}}\n\nAfter the gravity of Huckle's crimes became known, the Malaysian Government set up a telephone hotline for people to call if they have any information about Huckle or if they were abused themselves.<ref>{{cite news|title=Hotline set up for info on British paedophile Richard Huckle|url=http://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2016/06/02/hotline-set-up-for-info-on-british-paedophile-richard-huckle/|work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]|location=Malaysia|date=2 June 2016}}</ref> The Malaysian Prime Minister, [[Najib Razak]], added that he was angered and saddened by Huckle's sexual violation of Malaysian children and called for all parties involved to ensure that children are not exposed to situations where irresponsible people can take advantage of them.<ref>{{cite news|title=Najib: Heed lessons from Richard Huckle case|url=http://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2016/06/08/najib-heed-lessons-from-richard-huckle-case/|work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]|location=Malaysia|date=8 June 2016}}</ref> In August 2016, in response to the criticism following the Huckle case, Najib Razak announced that a special task force had been set up to investigate how Malaysia's child protection laws could be redrafted to take into account the new ways that child sexual predators such as Huckle were preying on Malaysian children,<ref>{{cite news|title=PMO sets up task force to review child protection laws|url=http://www.themalaymailonline.com/malaysia/article/pmo-sets-up-task-force-to-review-child-protection-laws|work=[[The Malay Mail]]|date=25 August 2016}}</ref> with the aim of having a new version ready by the end of the year.{{Update inline|date=February 2018}}\n\nFollowing the discovery of Huckle's crimes, the Malaysian Government came under fire from child protection charities for their lack of laws against child abuse and child pornography. James Nayagam, chairman of Suriana Welfare Society for Children, was particularly critical of his government's relaxed nature in dealing with such crimes:<ref name=starmalaysiacriticism>{{cite news|title=Have laws on child porn or another Richard Huckle|url=http://www.thestar.com.my/news/nation/2016/06/03/have-laws-on-child-pornography-or-another-richard-huckle/|work=[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]|location=Malaysia|date=3 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n{{quote|Malaysia should make child pornography and child sexual abuse a severe crime with heavy penalties. We should also issue a severe warning at the point of entering the country about our strong stance. Huckle got away with it. He knew the relaxed atmosphere in this country. We Asians fall head over heels with foreigners. He had people fall into his trap. But regardless of where people come from, we must have that check and balance.|author=James Nayagam|source=A newspaper article<ref name=starmalaysiacriticism />}}\n\nIn the article, Nayagam continued by pointing out that Section 292 of the Penal Code only deals with sale and distribution of obscene material.<ref name=starmalaysiacriticism />\n\nWhile the media in the UK were largely supportive of Huckle's sentencing, the Malaysian press widely stated that the punishment was not severe enough, with statements such as \"a thousand years is not enough\", \"We are horrified that the sex fiend [Huckle] will be eligible to appear before a parole board after 23 years\", and \"this monster could be out in 24 years\" appearing in the days after his sentence was announced.<ref>{{cite news|title=Malaysians say harsher sentence needed for Britain's 'worst paedophile' Richard Huckle|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2016/06/07/malaysians-say-harsher-sentence-needed-for-britains-worst-paedop/ |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=7 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=\u20181,000 years not enough\u2019 for jailed pedophile Richard Huckle \u2013 Malaysian media|url=https://www.rt.com/uk/345669-huckle-prison-malaysia-abuse/|publisher=[[RT (TV Network)|RT]]|date=7 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Death ==\n\nOn 13 October 2019, Huckle was found strangled and stabbed to death in his cell at [[HM Prison Full Sutton|Full Sutton]] prison, aged 33.<ref name=\"guardian-death\" /><ref>{{cite news |date= 14 October 2019 |title= Richard Huckle: Paedophile killed in prison 'strangled and stabbed' |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-50072903 |publisher= BBC News |access-date= 16 October 2019}}</ref> Another prisoner was charged with his murder in January 2020.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/amp/uk-england-humber-51239756|title=Richard Huckle jail killing: Inmate charged with murder|date=January 24, 2020|work=BBC News}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* \"[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sF9-r4JjRBw Richard Huckle stabbing: Portrait of a Paedophile]\" \u2013 [[Sky News]] documentary ([https://web.archive.org/web/20160606211554/https://news.sky.com/video/1705530/huckle-portrait-of-a-paedophile profile])\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Huckle, Richard}}\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:2019 deaths]]\n[[Category:21st-century English criminals]]\n[[Category:British people convicted of sexual assault]]\n[[Category:English people convicted of rape]]\n[[Category:Prisoners sentenced to life imprisonment by England and Wales]]\n[[Category:English Christians]]\n[[Category:English people convicted of child pornography offences]]\n[[Category:English people convicted of child sexual abuse]]\n[[Category:English photographers]]\n[[Category:English prisoners sentenced to life imprisonment]]\n[[Category:English sex offenders]]\n[[Category:English people who died in prison custody]]\n[[Category:English murder victims]]\n[[Category:British expatriates in Malaysia]]\n[[Category:Child grooming]]\n[[Category:Crime in Malaysia]]\n[[Category:Crime in Kuala Lumpur]]\n[[Category:Child sexual abuse scandals in religions]]\n[[Category:Deaths by stabbing in England]]\n[[Category:Teachers of English as a second or foreign language]]\n[[Category:Child pornography]]\n[[Category:People educated at The Harvey Grammar School]]\n[[Category:People murdered in England]]\n[[Category:Prisoners murdered in custody]]\n[[Category:Prisoners who died in England and Wales detention]]\n[[Category:Inmates of HM Prison Belmarsh]]\n", "name_user": "2a00:23c4:e889:5600:e5e8:b49b:9e5e:f9a5", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Richard_Huckle"}
